The paper focuses on a category-theoretic formalism for a class of neural networks, exemplified by CycleGAN, which is a popular approach in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and information theory (cs.IT).
